  "honest_verdict": "DOES NOT SURVIVE. The single surviving external win (mouse-KO, AUROC 0.687) was scored on the Check-A free-text adjudication surrogate (claude_go), not the committed commit_gate.evaluate output. When the REAL default-deny binary gate (GA>=0.20 AND celltype_matched_eqtl>0, trust non-binding) is scored against the hash-frozen mouse-immune axis (n=39, 28 pos, record-only), it gives MCC=-0.15 / balanced-acc 0.44 / AUROC 0.435 -- WORSE than the best function-blind baseline (random MCC~0; eQTL-threshold -0.04; OT-threshold -0.22). Advantage -0.15, permutation p=0.68, bootstrap 95% CI [-0.49, +0.05] (spans/below 0). At universe scale the literal gate GO's metabolic T1D/T2D genes that clear GA>=0.20 with eQTLs but have no mouse immune phenotype (SUOX, TCF7L2, CDKAL1, IRS1, GSDMB) and WITHHOLDS canonical immune genes (IL2, ICOS, PRKCQ, PTPN2, TNFAIP3) lacking a GA/eQTL floor hit. This is the SAME surrogate-vs-real-gate substitution that retracted the drug-target win. Reported plainly per the honesty contract: the mouse-KO win is an artifact of scoring the adjudicator, not the committed gate.",
